{"title_page": "Antonio Doncel", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name= Antonio Doncel\n|fullname= Antonio Doncel Valc\u00e1rcel\n|birth_date= 30 January 1967\n|birth_place= [[Province of Lugo|A Pobra de San Xiao]], [[Spain]]\n|position= [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n|height = 1.83m\n|years1= \n|clubs1= [[CD Lugo]]<ref>[http://www.futboldelugo.com/2014/12/hace-30-anos-que-cabo-dejo-el-futbol.html Hace 30 a\u00f1os que Cabo dej\u00f3 el f\u00fatbol, pero sigui\u00f3 en el CD Lugo] F\u00fatbol de Lugo</ref>\n|years2= 198x-1993\n|clubs2= [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a]]<ref>[https://www.rcdeportivo.es/noticia/anosahistoria-hace-30-anos-que-el-depor-jugaba-su-primera-semifinal-de-copa #ANosaHistoria: Hace 30 a\u00f1os que el D\u00e9por jugaba su primera semifinal de Copa] P\u00e1gina Oficial del R.C. Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a</ref>\n|caps2= 114\n|goals2= 2\n|years3= 1993-1994\n|clubs3= [[Real Burgos CF]]<ref>[http://realburgos.es/30o-aniversario-ascenso-a-primera-division-jornada-9a/ 30\u00ba ANIVERSARIO ASCENSO A PRIMERA DIVISI\u00d3N: JORNADA 9\u00aa] Real Burgos CF SAD</ref>\n|caps3= 29\n|goals3= 0\n|years4= 1994-1995\n|clubs4= [[Levante UD]] \n|caps4= 17\n|goals4= 0\n|years5= 1995-1996\n|clubs5= [[Racing de Ferrol]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://historiasracinguistas.blogspot.com/2008/09/antonio-doncel.html|title=Historia Racinguista: ANTONIO DONCEL|first=Historias|last=Racinguistas|date=September 29, 2008}}</ref>\n|caps5= 22\n|goals5= 1\n|years6= 1996-1998\n|clubs6= [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]]<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/dundee-united-sign-neil-duffy-from-rivals-dundee-1308762.html Dundee United sign Neil Duffy from rivals Dundee] The Independent</ref>\n|caps6= 37\n|goals6= 2\n|years7= 2001-2002\n|clubs7= [[Berganti\u00f1os FC]]\n\n}}\n\n'''Antonio Doncel''' (born 30 January 1967 in [[Spain]]) is a Spanish retired footballer who last played for [[Berganti\u00f1os FC|Berganti\u00f1os]] in his home country.<ref>[https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/carballo/2001/12/03/ex-deportivista-antonio-ficha-bergantinos-intentar-ascenso/0003_860238.htm El ex-deportivista Antonio ficha por el Berganti\u00f1os para intentar el ascenso] La Voz de Galicia</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nDoncel started his senior career with [[CD Lugo]]. In 1996, he signed for [[Hull City A.F.C.]] in the English [[Football League Third Division]], where he made forty-three appearances and scored two goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=9903|title=Antonio Doncel &#124; Football Stats &#124; No Club &#124; Age 52 &#124; 1988-1998 &#124; Soccer Base|website=www.soccerbase.com}}</ref> After that, he played for Spanish club [[Berganti\u00f1os FC|Berganti\u00f1os]] before retiring in 2002.\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See [[Wikipedia:Footnotes]] on how to create references using<ref></ref> tags which will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/deportes/2008/05/26/jugue-gran-orgullo-era-ciudad-the-housemartins-recuerda-gallego-antonio/0003_6850658.htm \u00abCuando jugu\u00e9 all\u00ed, su gran orgullo era ser la ciudad de The Housemartins\u00bb, recuerda el gallego Antonio] \n* [https://theguardian.newspapers.com/image/260900234/?terms=%22Antonio%2BDoncel%22 Spanish practices find a new home] \n* [https://quiosco.lavozdegalicia.es/historico.htm?fechaInicio=16-12-1991&fechaFin=16-11-2019&textoBusqueda=%22Antonio%20Doncel%22&orden=2 Dal Depor a la inglesa] \n* [https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/carballo/2001/12/29/antonio-continua-estirpe-ex-deportivistas-bergantinos/0003_893173.htm Antonio contin\u00faa la estirpe de los ex-deportivistas en el Berganti\u00f1os] \n* [https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/torremarathon/2019/03/28/heroes-superdepor/00031553776559527243756.htm \u00bfQu\u00e9 fue de los h\u00e9roes del Superd\u00e9por?] \n* [https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/j/j212.html 