l.html|title=Historia Racinguista: ANTONIO DONCEL|first=Historias|last=Racinguistas|date=September 29, 2008}}</ref>\n|caps5= 22\n|goals5= 1\n|years6= 1996-1998\n|clubs6= [[Hull City A.F.C.]]<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/dundee-united-sign-neil-duffy-from-rivals-dundee-1308762.html Dundee United sign Neil Duffy from rivals Dundee] The Independent</ref>\n|caps6= 37\n|goals6= 2\n|years7= 2001-2002\n|clubs7= [[Berganti\u00f1os FC]]\n\n}}\n\n'''Antonio Doncel''' (born 30 January 1967 in [[Spain]]) is a Spanish retired footballer who last played for [[Berganti\u00f1os FC|Berganti\u00f1os]] in his home country.<ref>[https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/carballo/2001/12/03/ex-deportivista-antonio-ficha-bergantinos-intentar-ascenso/0003_860238.htm El ex-deportivista Antonio ficha por el Berganti\u00f1os para intentar el ascenso] La Voz de Galicia</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nDoncel started his senior career with [[CD Lugo]]. In 1996, he signed for [[Hull City A.F.C.]] in the English [[Football League Third Division]], where he made forty-three appearances and scored two goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=9903|title=Antonio Doncel &#124; Football Stats &#124; No Club &#124; Age 52 &#124; 1988-1998 &#124; Soccer Base|website=www.soccerbase.com}}</ref> After that, he played for Spanish club [[Berganti\u00f1os FC|Berganti\u00f1os]] before retiring in 2002.\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See [[Wikipedia:Footnotes]] on how to create references using<ref></ref> tags which will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/deportes/2008/05/26/jugue-gran-orgullo-era-ciudad-the-housemartins-recuerda-gallego-antonio/0003_6850658.htm \u00abCuando jugu\u00e9 all\u00ed, su gran orgullo era ser la ciudad de The Housemartins\u00bb, recuerda el gallego Antonio] \n* [https://theguardian.newspapers.com/image/260900234/?terms=%22Antonio%2BDoncel%22 Spanish practices find a new ho